Algorithm: Train/Bus Route Management System

Step 1: Start
Initialize head = NULL
Initialize stack (top = -1)

Step 2: Display Menu
Show options:
Add Station
Insert at Position
Delete Station
Display Route
Reverse Display
Search Station
Total Distance
Total Fare
Travel Simulation
Show History
Exit

Step 3: Read User Choice
Input choice ch

Step 4: Perform Operation (Switch Case)
   Case 1: Add Station
Create new node
If list empty → make it head
Else → insert at end
   Case 2: Insert at Position
Create new node
Traverse to position
Insert node at given position
   Case 3: Delete Station
Search node by name
If found:
Adjust links
Delete node
Else → print "Not Found"
   Case 4: Display Route
Traverse linked list
Print each station
   Case 5: Reverse Display
Traverse list and push names into stack
Pop and display (reverse order)
   Case 6: Search Station
Traverse list
If found → print "Found"
Else → print "Not Found"
   Case 7: Total Distance
Traverse list
Add all distances
Display total
   Case 8: Total Fare
Traverse list
Add all fares
Display total
   Case 9: Travel Simulation
Traverse list
Print each station reached
Push into stack (for history)
   Case 10: Show History
Pop all elements from stack
Display travel history
   Case 11: Exit
Stop program

Step 5: Repeat
Go back to menu until user exits
